################################################################################
# 1. Requirements
################################################################################
	- python
	- python-twistd-words
	- python-twistd-conch
	- python-twistd-web
	- python-yaml
	- python-pyopenssl (for ssl-connections)
	- python-crypto (for ssl-connections)
	
	optional (only needed for some plugins):
	- feed: python-feedparser
	- ki: megahal (if megahal is used)
	- svn: pysvn
	- tv: python-xmltv (http://www.funktronics.ca/python-xmltv/)
	- weather: pywapi (http://code.google.com/p/python-weather-api/)
	- youtube: python-feedparser
	- zitat: python-feedparser

################################################################################
# 2. Setup
################################################################################
	First, to generate a config file, just run
		twistd gen-otfbot-config
	and answer the questions.
	After that, by default, all plugins will be enabled. If you want to disable
	some of them or just want to add another network or channel, edit the config
	file called 'otfbot.yaml'. Just delete the plugins listed in
	main.ircClientPlugins you don't want to use. To add further channels or
	networks see the first network at the end of the configfile.
	(Remind: one indentation are two spaces)

################################################################################
# 3. Starting
################################################################################
	To start up after configuring, just type
		twistd otfbot
	and the bot will start and connect to the configured networks and channels.
	That's all!

################################################################################
# 4. Developing plugins
################################################################################
	OtfBot is very easy extendable by developing your own plugins.
	Just have a look at example/example.py.
	All Callbacks are listed in this file. If you aren't sure what a
	specific callback does, just copy the plugin to otfbot/plugins/ircClient/,
	add it to config and start otfbot to test it.
	If you have finished follow the steps to enable a plugin above.
	If you think your plugin is of general interest, you are welcome to contact
	us and send us your plugin.

################################################################################
